## Stations by clicks

> **Syntax:**

```json
<%= config[:api_server] %>/xml/stations/topclick
<%= config[:api_server] %>/xml/stations/topclick/rowcount
```

```xml
<%= config[:api_server] %>/json/stations/topclick
<%= config[:api_server] %>/json/stations/topclick/rowcount
```

> **Results:**

> Array of struct '[station](#station)'

> **Example:**

```json
<%= config[:api_server] %>/json/stations/topclick
<%= config[:api_server] %>/json/stations/topclick/5
```

```xml
<%= config[:api_server] %>/xml/stations/topclick
<%= config[:api_server] %>/xml/stations/topclick/5
```

A list of the stations that are clicked the most. You can add a parameter with the number of wanted stations, supported output formats: JSON, XML, CSV, M3U, PLS, XSPF, TTL

### Parameters:

| Name | Default value | Possible value | Description |
|------|---------------|----------------|-------------|
| `limit` | `100000` | `0`,`1`,`2`,`3`,... | number of returned datarows (stations) starting with offset |
| `hidebroken` | `false` | `true`, `false` | do list/not list broken stations |
